This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it focuses on improving the readability of generated text in image captioning using natural language prior. It also involves language modeling and evaluation of generated text. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) because it deals with image captioning, which is a task in computer vision. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category because the paper proposes a solution to improve the performance of reinforcement learning in image captioning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category because the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance of image captioning. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category because the paper involves the evaluation of generated text using human evaluation, which is a common practice in information retrieval research.
